05/05/2003
RHODES, Greece -- Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul said Sunday (4 May) that all EU foreign ministers told him accession negotiations with Turkey would begin at the end of next year. 
Gul attended a two-day informal meeting of the EU Council of Foreign Ministers on the Greek island of Rhodes. 
After meeting with a number of them, Gul said a new page has been opened in relations between Turkey and the Union. 
He pledged that his government would use the next 18 months to maximise Turkey's chances for successful completion of the accession negotiations. 
(Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 04/05/03)
